    "body": "for issue #841\r\n\r\nThis pull request introduces a new CUDA read-only cache load intrinsic (`__ldg`) to the TileLang language, allowing users to explicitly request cached loads for performance-sensitive memory accesses. The implementation covers the TileLang Python API, CUDA and HIP code generation, documentation, and testing. Additionally, the pull request includes minor formatting improvements and error message clarifications in the codebase.\r\n\r\n### New CUDA Read-Only Cache Load Intrinsic\r\n\r\n* Added the `__ldg` intrinsic to TileLang, allowing explicit use of CUDA's read-only data cache for loads. This includes a Python API (`T.__ldg`), registration as a TileLang builtin, and documentation on usage and arguments. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32R62-R90) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-154d65bdd2298cc46b3f9719ce3627a35ec79f3a20c759f4c3211b67f9221564R99) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-77f0be35bfe359f85f32631aeb22db3337381c1da1676eca0da6c8588de94964R603-R620) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-39f3332b8026cdf6f2a0bcd6b507e46f4347e6e071b6a76668d4b7cec4b8f73eR371-R375)\r\n* Implemented backend code generation for `__ldg`:\r\n  - On CUDA, emits `__ldg(&buffer[idx])` for 1D buffer loads.\r\n  - On HIP, falls back to a regular load.\r\n* Added a Python test to verify that the CUDA code generator emits the correct `__ldg` intrinsic for eligible loads.\r\n\r\n### Code Formatting and Error Handling Improvements\r\n\r\n* Improved formatting and consistency in function definitions and error messages in `tilelang/language/builtin.py`, including clearer multi-line error messages and argument validation. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L403-R435) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L433-R469) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L491-R525) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L506-R541) [[5]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L554-R590) [[6]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L592-R629) [[7]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L719-R757) [[8]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L731-R769) [[9]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L752-R791) [[10]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L766-R805) [[11]](diffhunk://#diff-686c113e8a92c61ddb51c63c39887fe9a89f0ca4794cab91a168be4f2c1c2e32L783-R833)\r\n* Updated code style settings in `pyproject.toml` to enforce consistent indentation and argument splitting.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n## Release Notes\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Added `__ldg` intrinsic for explicit read-only cached loads in CUDA kernels. Optimizes memory access patterns by leveraging CUDA's specialized read-only cache. Accepts BufferLoad or Buffer with index arguments, with automatic fallback on non-CUDA backends.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added code generation tests validating `__ldg` integration with CUDA and HIP backends.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
